{"serial": "12016", "department_serial": 11, "code": "EL3071", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Cross-Linguistic Comparisons A", "ch": "跨語言對比分析A"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Li, Ming-Yi"], "ch": ["李明懿"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["2", "3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "A", "room": "110"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": 50, "department": {"ch": "英美語文學系", "en": "Department of English"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 19, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "本課程將聚焦在以中、英文為主的跨語言對比分析的方法和應用上。學生修習本課程並通過期末成績評核，應能具備以下能力：\n1. 能理解語言對比分析的基本理論和概念\n2. 能從詞彙、語法、語義和語用等面向進行跨語言觀察和分析\n3. 能增強對語言結構和功能的理解，培養對語言特徵的敏感度\n4. 能應用語料庫資源以及研究方法(資料收集和數據分析等)進行對比分析\n5. 能探索語言使用規約並應用於實際語言學習和教學中，以提高跨語言溝通能力和教學技巧。", "en": "This course will focus on the methods and applications of cross-language comparative analysis, mainly in Chinese and English.\nStudents who take this course and pass the final grade assessment should be able to possess the following abilities:\n1. Be able to comprehend the basic theories and concepts of contrastive analysis (CA).\n2. Be able to conduct cross-language observation and analysis from the aspects of vocabulary, grammar, semantics and pragmatics.\n3. Can enhance understanding of language structure and function, and cultivate sensitivity to language features\n4. Be able to apply corpus and research methods (data collection and data analysis, etc.) for CA.\n5. Be able to explore language usage conventions and apply them to actual language learning and teaching to improve cross-language communication skills and teaching skills."}, "outline": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "textbook": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "selfCompiledRate": {"ch": "0", "en": "0"}, "instructMethod": {"ch": "", "en": [""]}, "gradMethod": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "officeHour": {"ch": "週一13:00-15:00，週